BETWEEN
THE
ANTIBODY
RESPONSE
AND
THE
PROGNOSIS
OF
THE
PATIENTS
WAS
NOT
FOUND
AS
REGARDS
E
COLI
OR
B
FRAGILIS
CONSIDERING
THE
HYPOTHESIS
OF
WALLWORK
AND
COWORKERS
CONCERNING
INCREASED
ABSORPTION
OF
ANTIGENS
FROM
THE
GUT
IT
SEEMS
MORE
ATTRACTIVE
TO
SUPPOSE
THAT
INCREASED
ABSORPTION
OF
ANTIGENS
FROM
THE
GUT
FLORA
OCCURS
PREDOMINANTLY
IN
CF
PATIENTS
WITH
P
AERUGINOSA
LUNG
